  "authors": [],
  "body": {
    "comment": "I voted YES because Eternl is important Cardano infrastructure. Users rely on it for staking, governance, payments, and DApp access, so keeping it secure, stable, updated, and available benefits the whole ecosystem.\n\nI also like that the proposal includes a path toward sustainability through Eternl Pro while keeping a basic version free. This looks like temporary support for a real product with real users, not an open-ended dependency on treasury funding.\n\nCardano needs strong wallets, strong infrastructure, and builders who can keep improving through market cycles. Eternl is one of those tools, and that is why I supported it.\n"
  },
  "hashAlgorithm": "blake2b-256"
}